# Function Documentation Standard

For every new or modified function, add a short doc comment directly above it.

The comment must include:
- Inputs: key parameters and expected types/shape
- Outputs: return value, side effects, and thrown errors (if any)
- Internal: a brief summary of how the function works internally

Use concise, human-readable language. Keep docs accurate and updated when function behavior changes.

## Template

```js
/**
 * <One-line purpose>
 * Inputs: <paramName: type/meaning, ...>
 * Outputs: <return type/value, side effects, errors>
 * Internal: <brief approach/algorithm in plain language>
 */
```

## Example

```js
/**
 * Builds a terrain height value from layered simplex noise.
 * Inputs: x/y/z world coordinates (number), octaves (number).
 * Outputs: normalized height number in roughly [-1, 1], no side effects.
 * Internal: accumulates multiple noise octaves with halving amplitude and doubling frequency.
 */
function sampleHeight(x, y, z, octaves = 6) {
  // ...
}
```
